The course is build up as modules - there is short overview about each theme and practical exercises. Main communication skills (active listening, self-disclosure, etc) and main communication situations (assertiveness, conflict management, negotiation etc) will be discussed and exercised.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop communication skills, to support development of selfconsciousness and to improve skills needed in working as psychologists. Students will have knowledge about main social skills and can practise them successfully in their everyday lives.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students know and can put into practice the main social skills. Can evaluate and analyze his/her social competency. Can plan and conduct behavior in social situations.
